-- European Stocks Decline for Fourth Day, Led by Travel Companies, Miners
-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 2010-09-30T15:34:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/european-stocks-fall-for-fourth-day-benchmark-stoxx-600-closes-0-3-lower.html
European stocks declined for a
fourth straight day, trimming their monthly advance, as travel
companies and basic-resources producers retreated.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index dropped 0.3 percent to 260.15 at
4:33 p.m. in London, having earlier risen as much as 1.1
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
